46
00:03:34,756 --> 00:03:37,757
Uhh...

47
00:03:37,790 --> 00:03:39,798
What happened to your face?

48
00:03:39,831 --> 00:03:40,966
Pool game the other night.

49
00:03:40,999 --> 00:03:44,768
Called the wrong dude
on cheating.

50
00:03:44,802 --> 00:03:47,103
You got to watch that.

51
00:03:49,902 --> 00:03:52,677
What do you want again?

52
00:03:52,710 --> 00:03:54,938
I'm repping some people.

53
00:03:54,971 --> 00:03:57,747
Yeah. They want to get
to the good cook.

54
00:03:57,780 --> 00:03:59,613
They'll trade you
or the IC Brotherhood,

55
00:03:59,646 --> 00:04:02,781
however you want to do it,
coke for crystal.

56
00:04:05,824 --> 00:04:07,727
Why am I not talking to Miles?

57
00:04:07,761 --> 00:04:10,793
Oh, me and Ginger go way back,

58
00:04:10,834 --> 00:04:13,929
boosted together.

59
00:04:13,970 --> 00:04:15,570
You ain't saying much.

60
00:04:15,604 --> 00:04:17,971
I figure I let my man
give you the details.

61
00:04:18,004 --> 00:04:19,938
Look.
This shit I got,

62
00:04:19,971 --> 00:04:22,107
you can step on it 5, 6 times.

63
00:04:22,140 --> 00:04:23,675
It'll still kick.

64
00:04:23,716 --> 00:04:25,746
Just means you got
to cook a little more

65
00:04:25,779 --> 00:04:28,848
for a lot more profit.

66
00:04:30,713 --> 00:04:32,890
Nah.

67
00:04:32,923 --> 00:04:34,924
I ain't go no use for it

68
00:04:34,957 --> 00:04:36,355
or your money.

69
00:04:36,388 --> 00:04:38,856
What, money don't spend?

70
00:04:40,560 --> 00:04:45,000
I can see your soul
at the edges of your eyes.

71
00:04:45,033 --> 00:04:49,029
It's corrosive, like acid.

72
00:04:49,062 --> 00:04:51,996
You got a demon, little man,

73
00:04:52,037 --> 00:04:54,004
and I don't like your face.

74
00:04:54,037 --> 00:04:56,905
It makes me want
to do things to it.

75
00:04:58,234 --> 00:05:02,069
Ginger, you call me again,
I'm setting Miles on you.

76
00:05:04,142 --> 00:05:07,241
I see you again,

77
00:05:07,274 --> 00:05:09,979
I'm putting you down.

78
00:05:10,012 --> 00:05:12,411
There's a shadow on you, son.

79
00:05:38,178 --> 00:05:40,378
Marty, you got him?

80
00:05:40,411 --> 00:05:42,588
You fucking better, the
shit I've been though.

81
00:05:42,621 --> 00:05:44,853
I do. I got him.

82
00:05:44,886 --> 00:05:46,053
We're on empty roads now.

83
00:05:46,086 --> 00:05:48,759
So I got to drop back,
or he'll spot the tail.

84
00:05:48,792 --> 00:05:49,993
Okay. That's
Reggie Ledoux's

85
00:05:50,034 --> 00:05:51,729
cook partner Dewall.

86
00:05:51,770 --> 00:05:52,802
Birddog him, Marty.

87
00:05:52,835 --> 00:05:53,972
You got it.

88
00:05:54,005 --> 00:05:55,507
What's your location?

89
00:05:55,540 --> 00:05:58,905
Just south of I-10 along
the Creole Nature Trail

90
00:05:58,938 --> 00:06:00,506
heading towards Carlyss.

91
00:06:00,539 --> 00:06:01,611
Hurry up, man.

92
00:06:01,644 --> 00:06:04,186
Copy that.
On my way.

93
00:06:18,658 --> 00:06:20,929
How we doing
back there, Ginger?

94
00:06:20,962 --> 00:06:23,096
Fuck you, motherfucker.

95
00:06:24,233 --> 00:06:26,431
- Aah!
- Yeah.

96
00:06:29,766 --> 00:06:32,102
How'd you get onto Ledoux?

97
00:06:32,135 --> 00:06:34,208
One of my old CI's
tipped me off

98
00:06:34,241 --> 00:06:37,745
to the location
of his cook house.

99
00:06:37,778 --> 00:06:40,884
So I came back on the job.

100
00:06:42,420 --> 00:06:45,585
Didn't want anybody else
to catch him, bring him in.

101
00:06:47,921 --> 00:06:49,720
Look. You want my help?

102
00:06:49,761 --> 00:06:52,225
Just show me the rest
of the file.

103
00:06:52,258 --> 00:06:55,029
Why are you so hot to see
the new discovery file, man?

104
00:06:57,429 --> 00:06:59,491
Well, why are y'all...

105
00:06:59,531 --> 00:07:03,930
so hot to not give it to me?

106
00:07:03,963 --> 00:07:07,199
It's supposed to be like
a consultation, right?

107
00:07:07,232 --> 00:07:10,640
Yeah, but you go first.

108
00:07:10,673 --> 00:07:12,537
You take me through it,

109
00:07:12,570 --> 00:07:14,976
and I'll let you
see what we got.

110
00:07:18,808 --> 00:07:21,909
I'll hold you to that.

111
00:07:47,582 --> 00:07:49,115
Where's Ginger?

112
00:07:49,148 --> 00:07:51,949
Wrapped up in a ditch.
What you got?

113
00:07:51,982 --> 00:07:54,486
Well, lost him and then
had to double back

114
00:07:54,519 --> 00:07:57,020
a few times till
I found the exit.

115
00:07:57,053 --> 00:07:59,292
That's his truck there.

116
00:07:59,325 --> 00:08:02,228
We're gonna have
to call this in, Rust.

117
00:08:02,261 --> 00:08:04,165
Eh, we don't want to do that.

118
00:08:04,198 --> 00:08:06,261
Troops will come,
flood these woods.

119
00:08:06,302 --> 00:08:08,366
They could scatter.

120
00:08:09,840 --> 00:08:11,506
All right.

121
00:08:11,539 --> 00:08:13,546
We ain't gonna
find him from here.

122
00:08:19,190 --> 00:08:22,325
You ever been hunting, Marty?

123
00:08:22,358 --> 00:08:24,621
Uh, yeah--

124
00:08:24,661 --> 00:08:27,263
10-point buck
year before last,

125
00:08:27,296 --> 00:08:30,597
50 yards.

126
00:08:30,630 --> 00:08:32,467
I'm not talking about
sitting in a treehouse

127
00:08:32,500 --> 00:08:34,067
waiting to ambush a buck coming

128
00:08:34,100 --> 00:08:36,173
to sniff your gash bait.

129
00:08:36,206 --> 00:08:37,773
Talking about tracking.

130
00:08:37,806 --> 00:08:39,509
Jesus, you're a prick.

131
00:08:39,542 --> 00:08:41,277
Look. We find the place.
We come back here.

132
00:08:41,310 --> 00:08:42,645
We call it in.

133
00:08:42,678 --> 00:08:45,877
One of us stays
surveillance, yeah?

134
00:08:45,918 --> 00:08:48,613
I can live with that.

135
00:08:48,654 --> 00:08:50,718
Let's go.

136
00:08:50,752 --> 00:08:51,687
Now, you got a tip

137
00:08:51,720 --> 00:08:53,925
where Ledoux cooks,
and Cohle came back

138
00:08:53,958 --> 00:08:56,326
from wherever he was.

139
00:08:56,359 --> 00:08:58,495
You knew it was
gonna get here, man.

140
00:08:58,528 --> 00:09:01,264
Just the once,
the way you tell it.

141
00:09:02,903 --> 00:09:05,703
I'll tell it the same way
that I told the shooting board

142
00:09:05,736 --> 00:09:09,672
and every cop bar
between Houston and Biloxi,

143
00:09:09,705 --> 00:09:11,976
and you know why the story
is always the same

144
00:09:12,009 --> 00:09:13,914
17 years gone?

145
00:09:13,947 --> 00:09:16,786
Because it only went down
the one way.

146
00:09:18,356 --> 00:09:21,555
Now, Rust's dad taught him
bowhunting.

147
00:09:21,588 --> 00:09:24,995
You know, you had
to track game till you got

148
00:09:25,028 --> 00:09:27,762
within maybe 30 yards of it.

149
00:09:37,176 --> 00:09:41,647
Now, this enabled us
to discern the suspect's path

150
00:09:41,680 --> 00:09:45,446
while sidestepping various
anti-intruder devices

151
00:09:45,487 --> 00:09:48,285
they installed.

152
00:11:03,230 --> 00:11:07,062
Tripwires back there.
Clearing is probably mined.

153
00:11:07,103 --> 00:11:10,901
All right.
How you want to do it?

154
00:11:10,934 --> 00:11:16,508
You go back. Call it in.
I'll wait here.

155
00:11:16,541 --> 00:11:18,844
You're gonna hold position?

156
00:11:18,877 --> 00:11:20,909
Yep.

157
00:11:25,550 --> 00:11:28,057
Do it now, Marty.

158
00:11:28,090 --> 00:11:30,057
Fuck you.

159
00:11:30,090 --> 00:11:32,699
You ain't doing this
without me.

160
00:11:45,952 --> 00:11:48,447
All right.
Stay low.

161
00:11:53,158 --> 00:11:55,591
We were just about
to turn back,

162
00:11:55,624 --> 00:11:58,329
call in parish, state, whoever.

163
00:11:58,362 --> 00:12:00,262
I mean, we had the location.

164
00:12:00,295 --> 00:12:03,397
We had our suspects identified
at the location, you know?

165
00:12:03,430 --> 00:12:05,470
Might as well
just leave the shit be

166
00:12:05,503 --> 00:12:07,703
and hand it off.

167
00:12:07,736 --> 00:12:10,342
That ain't what happened.
Hmm.

168
00:12:12,007 --> 00:12:15,341
No. As soon as we started
to back off, man...

169
00:12:15,374 --> 00:12:17,077
Blam!

170
00:12:17,110 --> 00:12:19,182
Bullets cut through
right near Rust's head.

171
00:12:19,215 --> 00:12:22,886
We dove opposite ways
into the high growth,

172
00:12:22,919 --> 00:12:24,591
but they'd already spotted us,

173
00:12:24,624 --> 00:12:26,992
and they had something
high-velocity.

174
00:12:27,025 --> 00:12:30,697
Boom! Blew apart this tree
between us.

175
00:12:30,730 --> 00:12:32,730
I mean, it was on.

176
00:12:37,003 --> 00:12:38,402
Hmm.

177
00:12:38,435 --> 00:12:39,738
Heavy shit--

178
00:12:39,771 --> 00:12:41,938
like ferns and whatnot
bursting all around us,

179
00:12:41,979 --> 00:12:43,476
bark flying off of trees.

180
00:12:43,509 --> 00:12:45,884
I mean we were
in a bucket shitstorm.

181
00:13:09,404 --> 00:13:10,835
Shit.

182
00:14:07,051 --> 00:14:08,523
State police.

183
00:14:08,556 --> 00:14:10,891
Put your hands on your head.

184
00:14:10,925 --> 00:14:13,227
Put them on your head now.

185
00:14:13,260 --> 00:14:15,964
Don't even think about it.

186
00:14:15,997 --> 00:14:18,332
Put your hands
on your head right now.

187
00:14:18,365 --> 00:14:20,804
Intertwine your fingers.

188
00:14:20,837 --> 00:14:22,371
Do it.

189
00:14:22,404 --> 00:14:23,971
Back up toward me.

190
00:14:28,848 --> 00:14:31,551
Down on your knees.
Go on.

191
00:14:36,992 --> 00:14:40,225
It's time, isn't it?

192
00:14:40,258 --> 00:14:41,866
The black stars.

193
00:14:41,899 --> 00:14:43,697
Shut the fuck up.

194
00:14:56,685 --> 00:14:59,713
They'd spotted us
before we crossed the forest.

195
00:14:59,746 --> 00:15:03,752
So all we could do
was duck for cover, dig in,

196
00:15:03,785 --> 00:15:07,427
try getting closer.

197
00:15:07,460 --> 00:15:09,764
It was chaos.

198
00:15:28,281 --> 00:15:30,920
The black stars rise.

199
00:15:30,952 --> 00:15:32,981
Why the antlers?

200
00:15:38,927 --> 00:15:40,192
Freeze, motherfucker.

201
00:15:40,233 --> 00:15:43,603
Put it down. Hands up.
State police.

202
00:15:53,008 --> 00:15:54,773
Set it down.

203
00:15:54,806 --> 00:15:57,442
I know what happens next.

204
00:15:57,475 --> 00:15:59,875
I saw you in my dream.

205
00:15:59,908 --> 00:16:03,716
You're in Carcosa now with me.

206
00:16:03,749 --> 00:16:05,548
He sees you.

207
00:16:08,314 --> 00:16:10,354
Marty!

208
00:16:20,077 --> 00:16:22,811
You'll do this again.

209
00:16:22,844 --> 00:16:24,841
Time is a flat circle.

210
00:16:24,874 --> 00:16:26,914
Listen, Nietzsche.
Shut the fuck up.

211
00:16:26,947 --> 00:16:30,379
Put it down. Marty!

212
00:16:30,419 --> 00:16:32,386
There you go.

213
00:16:32,419 --> 00:16:34,818
Black star.

214
00:16:35,989 --> 00:16:38,862
Put your hands on your head.

215
00:17:06,884 --> 00:17:11,028
While I was hunkered down
behind this old, decrepit boat,

216
00:17:11,061 --> 00:17:13,294
Captain America Marty Hart

217
00:17:13,367 --> 00:17:15,031
decides he's gonna run
deep into the woods,

218
00:17:15,064 --> 00:17:16,630
flank around the back
of the house

219
00:17:16,663 --> 00:17:18,669
where Ledoux is firing
at us, right?

220
00:17:18,702 --> 00:17:20,701
Well, he sneaks up
behind Ledoux

221
00:17:20,734 --> 00:17:25,078
and just as Ledoux turns,
bam, popped one off in him--

222
00:17:25,111 --> 00:17:27,815
head shot, clean--
dropped him.

223
00:17:27,848 --> 00:17:30,817
Now, his buddy Dewall,
he made a run for it,

224
00:17:30,850 --> 00:17:34,690
and his homemade,
cracker-ass security system

225
00:17:34,723 --> 00:17:37,424
took care of the rest.

226
00:17:40,493 --> 00:17:43,300
Oh, fuck.

227
00:17:43,333 --> 00:17:45,270
Get the cuffs off him

228
00:17:45,303 --> 00:17:46,735
before his blood settles.

229
00:17:46,776 --> 00:17:48,911
We got to make this look right.

230
00:17:56,384 --> 00:17:59,216
Goddamn. Fuck.

231
00:18:23,116 --> 00:18:25,080
What do we do, Rust?

232
00:18:25,113 --> 00:18:26,480
Oh, fuck him.

233
00:18:26,513 --> 00:18:28,448
Good to see you
commit to something.

234
00:18:28,481 --> 00:18:29,784
Now go see to the kids.

235
00:18:29,817 --> 00:18:31,655
Don't bring them out
until I say so.

236
00:18:43,835 --> 00:18:46,707
After we confirmed two deaths

237
00:18:46,740 --> 00:18:49,571
and searched the rest
of the premises,

238
00:18:49,604 --> 00:18:52,472
that's when we found
the two children.

239
00:18:52,505 --> 00:18:55,073
I mean, we got very lucky.

240
00:18:55,114 --> 00:18:58,284
We just as easily
could've been chewed to pieces

241
00:18:58,317 --> 00:19:02,525
by an AK on approach.

242
00:19:15,729 --> 00:19:19,500
I can say that I walked
away from the experience

243
00:19:19,533 --> 00:19:25,301
with a greater respect
for the sanctity of human life.

244
00:19:25,342 --> 00:19:27,139
Yeah.

245
00:19:27,172 --> 00:19:28,634
Thank you, Detective.

246
00:19:28,675 --> 00:19:29,872
I believe I speak for the board

247
00:19:29,905 --> 00:19:31,136
when I commend you
on the heroism

248
00:19:31,169 --> 00:19:33,575
displayed by you
and Detective Hart.

249
00:19:35,610 --> 00:19:39,344
No. We were doing
our jobs, sir.

250
00:19:47,751 --> 00:19:52,989
There were the twig sculptures

251
00:19:53,022 --> 00:19:59,197
and the LSD on hand matched
that in Dora Lange.

252
00:19:59,230 --> 00:20:04,302
Everybody was pretty satisfied
that we got our man.

253
00:20:11,613 --> 00:20:16,043
The boy
had been missing since January.

254
00:20:16,076 --> 00:20:18,810
He'd been dead less than a day.

255
00:20:22,551 --> 00:20:25,517
The girl, she hadn't been
reported yet.

256
00:20:25,550 --> 00:20:30,319
She was from St. Landry,
catatonic when we found her.

257
00:20:36,627 --> 00:20:40,330
Why should I live
in history, huh?

258
00:20:40,363 --> 00:20:43,466
Fuck, I don't want to know
anything anymore.

259
00:20:43,499 --> 00:20:46,831
This is a world
where nothing is solved.

260
00:20:46,864 --> 00:20:50,539
Someone once told me,
"Time is a flat circle."

261
00:20:53,013 --> 00:20:56,211
Everything we've ever done
or will do

262
00:20:56,244 --> 00:20:57,813
we're gonna do over and over
